Background¶

This dataset is for customers who purchased Treadmill product(s) from a retail store called Cardio Good Fitness.

Objective¶

  • Come up with a customer profile (characteristics of a customer) for each Treadmill product
  • Perform uni-variate and multi-variate analyses
  • Generate a set of insights and recommendations that will help the company in targeting new customers

Key Questions to be Answered¶

  • Are there any differences between customers of each product?
  • Is there any relationship patterns that can be observed between the different attributes of customers?

Dataset¶

  • Product - the model no. of the treadmill
  • Age - in no of years, of the customer
  • Gender - of the customer
  • Education - in no. of years, of the customer
  • Marital Status - of the customer
  • Usage - Avg. # times the customer wants to use the treadmill every week
  • Fitness - Self rated fitness score of the customer (5 - very fit, 1 - very unfit)
  • Income - of the customer
  • Miles- expected to run

Important Observations¶

  • The maximum age of the customer purchasing the Treadmill products is 50 years old and age of 50% of the customers is 26 years old.
  • 50% of customers purchasing the Treadmill products gave self rated fitness on scale of 3.
  • 50% of customers have 16 years of education, which means they have at least college degree.
  • The median income of the customers is 50K USD per annum.
  • 50% of customers expect to run 94 miles per week.
  • 50% of customers expected usage of Treadmill is 3 times per week

Other Observations¶

  1. The Age of customers range from 18 years to 50 years
  2. The mean Age is larger than 50% percentile of the data, indicating a right skewed data distribution.
  3. The income has huge spread ranging from 29562 to 104581 USD per annum.
  4. The mean Income is close to 75% percentile of the data, indicating a right skewed data distribution.
  5. The mean Education is close to 50% percentile of the data, indicating symmetric data ranging from 12 years to 21 years
  6. The mean usage is close to 50% percentile of the data, indicating symmetric data ranging from 2 to 7 times per week.
  7. The mean self rated Fitness data is close to 50% percentile of the data, indicating symmetric data ranging from 1-to-5 scale, where 1 is poor shape and 5 is excellent shape

    • Education has few outliers at the higher end with few customers > 20 years of education.
    • Usage has few outliers at the higher end with few customers expected to use Treadmill 6 to 7 times a week
    • Most of the customers self rated their fitness at 3. There is outlier at the lower end with self rated fitness as poor at 1 scale.

Another way to visualize distribution of various numerical data using histogram plot with mean and median on the plots¶

In [13]:
# to visualize distribution of various important customer profile data (numerical data) using histogram plot of 
# Matplotlib package and plot the mean and median on the plot 
# mean = color code is red solid line
# median = color code is blue dotted line

cust_profile = ['Age', 'Education', 'Usage', 'Miles','Fitness','Income']
#list(enumerate(colors))
#  plot Numerical Data
a = 3  # number of rows
b = 2  # number of columns
c = 1  # initialize plot counter

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(14,22))
for i in cust_profile:
    plt.subplot(a, b, c)
    plt.title('{} (hist), subplot: {}{}{}'.format(i, a, b, c),fontsize=12,fontweight='bold')
    plt.hist(cardiofit[i],color='coral') 
    plt.axvline(cardiofit[i].mean(), color='r', linewidth=2)
    plt.axvline(cardiofit[i].median(), color='b', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)       
    c = c + 1
    continue

plt.show()

Observations¶

  • Mean customer age is 28 yeras old and Median is 26 years old. Most of the customers are < 35 years old. Customers drop > 35 years old.
  • Income: Mean income is 52K USD per annum larger than median income 50K USD per annum. Most of the customers fall in first 4 bins, that is in lower pay range < 60K USD per annum
  • Most of the customers expect to run 100 miles per week, mean and median is pretty close. Very few customers expect to run > 150 miles per week.
  • There is not much variance of data with Education, Fitness and Usage
  • Mean and Median self rated fitness scale is pretty close. Mean is 3.3 and Median is 3.0. Most of the customers fall in 3.0 bin
  • Mean expected usage of Treadmill is 3.4 and Median expected usage of Treadmill is 3.0. Most of the customers fall in the 3 days per week bin
  • Mean education is 16 years, close to the median. Most of the customers fall in the 16 years bin.

In [15]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
sns.heatmap(cardiofit.corr(), annot=True, vmin=-1, vmax=1, fmt=".2f", cmap="Spectral")
title = 'CORRELATION MATRIX OF CUSTOMER PROFILE\n'
plt.title(title, loc='center', fontsize=15)
plt.show()

Observations¶

  • Fitness has high positive correlation with average number of Miles the customer wants to run each week. This is expected.
  • Usage has high positive correlation with Miles which is again expected. More number of miles the customer wants to run, the higher usage of the product will be every week.
  • Fitness, Miles and Usage have high positive correlation with each other and are interdependant. As expected, all these values are highly correlated with each other.
  • Education has high positive correlation with Income. As expected, higher the education of the customer, higher is the income.
  • Fitness has fairly high positive correlation with Income. This shows that customers with better income self rated their fitness scale higher.
  • Age has least correlation with Usage
  • Fitness has least correlation with Age

Observations¶

  • For All 3 Treadmill models, both Male and Female (Partnered and Single) customers have same number of years of Education.
  • For All 3 Treadmill models, Partnered Male customers are in wider range of age group compared to Single Male customers. Whereas, with Female customers, Single and Partnered are in almost similar range of age group.
  • For TM195 Treadmill model, expected miles to run by Partnered Male customers is less compared to Single Male customers. Whereas, expected miles to run by Partnered Female customers is more than Single Female customers.
  • TM195 Treadmill model has the highest Single Male customers than other 2 Treadmill models
    • TM195 Treadmill model has more Single customers than Partnered customers
  • For TM498 and TM798 Treadmill models, expected miles to run by Partnered Female customers is more than Single Female customers. Except for TM195, expected miles to run by Single Female customers is slightly more than Partnered Female customers
  • Male customers expected to run more miles than Female customers
    • Single Male cusomers expect to run more miles than Partnered Male customers
    • But Partnered Female customers expect to run more miles than Single Female customers

Observations¶

  • Customers purchasing TM798 Treadmill model
    • Earn more income compared to customers purchasing other models. Partnered (Male & Female) customers earn beyound 80K USD per annum, which is the outliers we had seen in previous plots for income.
    • Expecting to use the Treadmill for more numbers of days per week (4 to 7 days per week) compared to 3 days per week usage by customers purchasing other models. This is the outliers we had seen for Usage in the previous plots.
    • Self rated their Fitness at a higher scale up to 5 compared to self rating at 3 by customers purchasing other models.
  • Customers purchasing TM195 and TM498 models
    • Earn lower income, less than 60K USD per annum
    • Expecting to use the Treadmill for same number of days per week (3 days per week).
    • Self rated their Fitnes at 3 scale.
  • Partnered customers earn more income
  • On an average, Male customers expect to use more Treadmill than Female customers
    • Single Male customers expect to use more Treadmill than Partnered Male customers
    • But Partnered Female customers expect to use more Treadmill than Single Female customers
  • Male customers self rated their fitness higher than Female customers
    • Single Male customers self rated their fitness higher than Partnered Male customers
    • But Partnered Female customers self rated their fitness higher than Single Female customers

Observations¶

  • Higher income customers ( > 70K USD per annum) purchased TM798 model
  • Lower income customers (< 60 K per annum) purchased TM195 and TM498 models
  • Higher Education customers ( 17 to 18 years of Education) puchased TM798 model. May be have advanced education after college
  • Up to 16 years of Education customers purchased TM195 and TM498 models. May be with 4 years of college degree
  • Higher self rated Fitness customers, up to scale 5, purchased TM798 model
  • Average self rated Fitness, up to 3, purchased TM195 and TM498 models
  • Higher age group customers, 26 to 33 years old, purchased TM498 model
  • Age group of 26 to 29 years old customers purchased TM195 and TM798 models
  • Customers with higher expected usage of Treadmill of up to 4 to 7 days a week purchased TM798 model
  • Customers with average expected usage of Treadmill of up to 3 days a week purchased TM195 and TM498 models
  • Customers with higher expected miles to run > 150 miles per week, purchased TM798 model
  • Customers with average expected miles to run of up to 100 miles per week, purchased TM195 and TM498 models

Customer Profile for Treadmill Model TM195¶

TM195 is the most purchased model, up to 80 sold.¶

  • Average income is ~47K USD per annum, less than 60K USD per annum
  • Average years of Education is 16 years. May be with 4 years of college degree
  • Self rated fitness is 3.0 on an average
  • Age ranging from 26 to 29 years old
  • Average usage of Treadmill is 3 days per week
  • Average number of miles expecting to run is 100 miles per week

Customer Profile for Treadmill Model TM498¶

TM498 is the second most purchased model, up to 60 sold.¶

  • Average income is ~47K USD per annum, less than 60K USD per annum
  • Average years of Education is 16 years. May be with 4 years of college degree
  • Self rated fitness is 3.0 on an average
  • Age ranging from 26 to 33 years old
  • Average usage of Treadmill is 3 days per week
  • Average number of miles expecting to run is 100 miles per week

Customer Profile for Treadmill model TM798¶

TM798 model is the least purchased model, only 40 sold.¶

  • Average income ~79K USD per annum, greater than 70K USD per annum and max up to 98K USD per annum.
  • Average years of Education is 17 to 18 years. May be with 2 years of advanced higher education after college
  • Self rated fitness is up to scale 5.0 (means very fit)
  • Age ranging from 26 to 29 years old
  • Average usage of Treadmill is 4 to 7 days per week
  • Average number of miles expecting to run is > 150 miles per week

Overall Observations¶

  • TM195 Treadmill model is the most purchased model with Total 80 customers. And has equal number of Male and Female customers.
  • TM498 Treadmill model is the second most purchased model with 60 customers. And has almost equal number of Male and * Female customers (Male count=31, Female count=29)
  • TM798 Treadmill model is the least purchased model with 40 customers. It has more Male customers (count = 33) and least Female customers (count = 7) compared to all other models.
  • All 3 Treadmill models have more Male customers than Female customers
    • Partnered customers are more than Single customers
  • All 3 Treadmill models have younger customers with average age of 28 years old. Customers drop > 35 years old. There are very few customers > 40 years old with max age of 50 years old
  • TM498 model has wider age group of customers(mostly Partnered Male customers).
  • Customers of TM195 and TM498 models are in lower pay range < 60K USD per annum, average education of 16 years, with average self rated fitness at 3.0, with average expecte usage of Treadmill of 3 days per week and expect to run < 100 miles per week
  • TM798 model has higher pay range customers > 70 K with max of 98KUSD per annum, with higher education of 17 to 18 yrs, higher self rated fitness at max of 5.0 (very fit), with higher usage of Treadmill of 4 to 7 days a week and higher miles expected to run > 150 miles per week
  • On an average, Male customers expect to use more Treadmill than Female customers
    • Single Male customers expect to use more Treadmill than Partnered Male customers.
    • But Partnered Female customers expect to use more Treadmill than Single Female customers.
  • Male customers self rated their fitness higher than Female customers
    • Single Male customers self rated their fitness higher than Partnered Male customers
    • But Partnered Female customers self rated their fitness higher than Single Female customers
  • Male customers expected to run more miles than Female customers
    • Single Male cusomers expect to run more miles than Partnered Male customers
    • But Partnered Female customers expect to run more miles than Single Female customers

Recommendations to increase sales¶

  • TM798 model is the least sold model and more purchased by higher income customers than lower income customers. Assuming the reason to be cost here. Advertise this model with reduced price offer on special holidays to make it more affordable for lower income customers.
  • Since the TM798 customers self rated thier fitness at higher scale, this might be one other reason for low sales of this product. Market additional features of the model to attract very fit customers like making it look more productive like spend less time to get more workout done.
  • Market the 3 Treadmill models to attract more customers in the age group > 35 years old with benefits of being fit and healthy as you grow older
  • To target more Female customers, market the Treadmill product online where the audience lives more online as per surveys. Use influencers to share the benefits of staying fit with women perspective.
  • Since Partnered Female customers self rate their fitness higher and expect to run more miles, target more Partnered female customers by advertising with family perspective ads and include installment payments.
  • Target customers with different advertsing stratergies like for male customers use more stats and for female customers use more emotions.
  • Market TM195 and TM498 to higher income and higher education customers by advertising it with different startergies ads with vibrant colors like making it look more branded model highlighting special features and benefits.
  • Single customers are less eventhough they expect to use more Treadmill and expect to run more. The reason may be because their self rated fitness is higher. Target more single customers by marketing the product on social media, start a friend referral program.
